description.narrative: Central educational institutions, as well as primary and secondary schools have the capacity to provide quality, inclusive and innovative services, which contributes to Access To Quality Learning Opportunities, Access To Quality Learning Opportunities (Covid), Education â€“ General, Equity â€“ Focus On Girls' And Inclusive Education, Learning And Child-Friendly Schools, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Girls and boys, especially those affected by poverty, adversity and exclusion, progressively utilise quality, inclusive and efficient education system reinforced by policies, programmes and services for empowerment and participation, by 2022.

description.narrative: All preschools and schools reopened in September 2021 due to the strong advocacy efforts by UNICEF. Critical support was provided to children with disabilities and Roma children to compensate for the learning loss through catch-up lessons, mentoring and tailor-made support measures. Digital School, the platform for online learning and teaching based on the Learning Passport prototype was launched, containing a variety of quality digital materials for children, teachers, and parents. Education Sector Analysis was finalized and will be published in 2022, to serve as a basis for developing an evidence-based, prioritized and financed multi-year sector plan | Status:On-track | As-of Date:23/01/2022
